Here's a fun story to help balance the sad...last summer an auction was held
for a couple who were retiring and returning to their homeland of Ireland
(where they had a nice stone farmhouse/lots of land waiting). They had
collected silver. All day long silver was sold - $500 here, $800 there -
about two a minute, I would say. Plus she had many, many other items. It
was the only auction I've ever attended where three phone lines were going
with bids coming in from all over the world. It was quite exciting. Well,
after I closed my mouth in awe from all of this I went down behind the house
to the &quot;cheap&quot; tent and found some fabulous treasures that went for under
$5. I knew the woman who was selling all of this and she was having a grand
time. She told me all about a the sculpture I had gotten for $2 (something
I would never, ever part with) - where she had gotten it, what it had meant
to her, etc. It was a wonderful day - for the rich who could afford the
silver and for me who stayed with my &quot;under $5&quot; budget!

Janeen

