This happened just last year....
My grandparents belongings were being auctioned off at the farm after my
grandmother died (grandpa had passed on ten years earlier).
I was interested in a little Fly Rod Mouse that was still in the box.
It reminded me of the days when Grandpa &amp; I would go to his pond &amp; I would fish
with a cane pole &amp; he would put on his waders &amp; cast with a fly rod.
This lure was real cute only about 2&quot; long, little beady eyes, furry ears,
tail, (you get the picture).
I started bidding on it from the start &amp; after it hit $65.00, most people
dropped out. One guy kept bidding. I just kept bidding until he finally quit. I
paid $145.00. After that, the guy came up to me &amp; said &quot;I had no idea that lure
was worth so much! Are you a dealer or something?&quot; I looked him square in the
eyes &amp; said &quot;No, I'm his grandson.&quot;
He walked away without saying another word.
