The truly sad thing about Estate auctions is the way proceeds are distributed.
The lawyer gets a cut...The executor gets a cut....The auctioneer gets a
cut...and Uncle Sam gets more than all of the above.
It seems to me that it would be more fair to identify all the belongings with a
number ...put the numbers in a hat and have the remaining family members draw
them at will. That way all the blood, sweat and tears that went into the years
of accumulating the family worth would remain just that.......&quot;family worth&quot;.
Each one has a piece..a memory.......
A sad auction story..........
